## 🧠 Model Parameters vs Training Settings

### Model Parameters (`model_params`)
**Definition:** Core neural network and learning settings that are SAVED WITH the model.

```json
{
  "policy": "MlpPolicy",           // Neural network architecture
  "learning_rate": 0.0003,         // How fast the AI learns
  "buffer_size": 200000,           // Memory of past experiences
  "batch_size": 512,               // Learning batch size
  "learning_starts": 5000,         // Exploration before learning
  "train_freq": 1,                 // Learning frequency
  "target_update_interval": 1000,  // Target network updates
  "exploration_fraction": 0.3,     // Exploration strategy
  "exploration_final_eps": 0.02,   // Final exploration rate
  "verbose": 1,                    // Logging level
  "tensorboard_log": "./tensorboard/",  // Metrics location
  "device": "cuda"                 // GPU/CPU selection
}
```

**Impact:** These fundamentally change HOW the AI learns and behaves.

### Training Settings (separate from model)
**Definition:** Control the training process duration and evaluation, NOT saved with model.

```json
{
  "total_timesteps": 100000,       // How long to train
  "eval_episodes": 20,             // Evaluation episode count
  "max_steps_per_episode": 500,    // Episode length limit
  "eval_freq": 5000,               // Evaluation frequency
  "checkpoint_save_freq": 25000    // Backup frequency
}
```

**Impact:** These control WHEN and HOW LONG training happens.

