## 🔄 Practical Training Workflows

### Scenario 1: Resume Training (Default)
```bash
# Uses existing models as-is, continues with same parameters
python ai/train.py --orchestrate --training-config debug
```
- ✅ Fastest startup
- ✅ Maintains exact training state
- ❌ Won't use updated config parameters

### Scenario 2: Update Training Configuration
```bash
# Loads models but updates them with current config
python ai/train.py --orchestrate --training-config conservative --append
```
- ✅ Keeps learned knowledge
- ✅ Uses updated parameters
- ⚠️ May need readjustment period

### Scenario 3: Fresh Start
```bash
# Creates completely new models
python ai/train.py --orchestrate --training-config aggressive --new
```
- ✅ Clean slate with new parameters
- ❌ Loses all previous learning
- 🕐 Takes longer to achieve competency

### Scenario 4: Experiment with Rewards
```bash
# Keep models, change only reward structure
python ai/train.py --orchestrate --rewards-config experimental
```
- ✅ Instant reward changes
- ✅ Maintains learned knowledge  
- 📊 Observe adaptation in Tensorboard

